&lt;p&gt;Scopely is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Lead Technical Artist&lt;/strong&gt; to join our unannounced project in person at our Culver City hub, or remotely within the US or Canada.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play, every day - whether in our work environments alongside our talented colleagues or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing, and innovating the mobile games industry, connecting millions of people worldwide daily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are in the early stages of development on an ambitious, unannounced, cross-platform Strategy/MMO featuring a well-known IP. You have the opportunity to join a highly experienced team to make a lasting impact on one of the next big releases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a hands-on Lead Technical Artist to help drive technical art direction, tools development, content pipelines, optimization efforts, and cross-disciplinary collaboration for a large-scale mobile, live service game project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role combines active technical contribution with team leadership. The ideal candidate is equally comfortable building tools, solving complex production challenges, guiding technical strategy, supporting artists and animators, and partnering with engineering, design, production, QA, outsourcing, and co-development teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a pure management role. We are looking for a technical leader who remains close to the work, enjoys solving problems directly, and can help make an entire development organization more effective.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly experienced in Technical Art, Tools Development, Pipeline Development, Game Development, or a related discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant hands-on experience building tools, scripts, automation, or pipeline systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience developing tools or workflows for Unity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with DCC tools such as Maya, Blender, Houdini, or similar.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with C#, Python, or similar scripting/programming languages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience optimizing game content for memory, performance, asset size, loading, or runtime efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of game content pipelines, asset integration, source control, and production workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading or mentoring Technical Artists, Technical Animators, Riggers, or similar technical content roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with outsourcing and/or co-development partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills and the ability to work across Art, Animation, Engineering, Design, Production, QA, and external teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with distributed teams across multiple time zones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Artists, animators, designers, and developers are unblocked quickly and supported by reliable workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tools and pipelines improve team efficiency and reduce repeated manual work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content is easier to create, validate, integrate, and optimize.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical risks are identified early and communicated clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The technical art team is well-supported, well-prioritized, and aligned with project goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Internal and external teams can deliver content that meets quality, workflow, and performance expectations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The project has a clear technical art direction that balances creativity, production needs, and platform realities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hands-On Technical Art Development&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintai

&lt;p&gt;Scopely is looking for a&amp;nbsp;Lead Game Designer to join our Monopoly GO! game team remotely within the US!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play, every day - whether in our work environments alongside our talented colleagues, or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing and innovating the mobile games industry, connecting millions of people around the world daily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monopoly GO! is a global phenomenon and the biggest mobile game launch in history, captivating millions of players worldwide. The team is based in Europe and the US, and works every day to create captivating new experiences for our players.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own product features end-to-end — from early concept through release, live operations, and post-launch optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the creation of new multiplayer social and/or solo minigames that expand player engagement and enrich the overall gameplay experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate high-level product and franchise objectives into detailed, player-centric feature designs, ensuring clarity and alignment across teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain clear, comprehensive game and feature specifications, partnering closely with design to ensure documentation is complete, consistent, and actionable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with design and UX, guiding the direction of designs and ensuring they reflect player needs, franchise goals, and business priorities (without directly managing designers day-to-day).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work deeply cross-functionally with designers, artists, engineers, analysts, and producers to build high-quality features that meet both product and technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ongoing feedback and implementation support, ensuring features progress smoothly through development and match the intended vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay on top of market, genre, and competitive trends to shape an innovative, data-informed roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate strong leadership, influencing team direction, driving alignment, and elevating the quality of execution—beyond just generating ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Potentially mentor or partner closely with designers, with room to grow into management responsibilities over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for F2P Mobile Games: Enthusiastic about working on sophisticated F2P ecosystems, handling diverse player life cycles and spending behaviors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience &amp;amp; Qualifications: 5+ years in F2P mobile casual games&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication Skills: Strong verbal and written skills; able to explain the “why” to align the team with the product vision; ability to thrive in global team environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project Management: Skilled at prioritizing high-impact initiatives, understanding trade-offs, anticipating risks, managing expectations, and ensuring quality deliverables&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feature Ownership: Exemplified experience in leading indirect reports toward shared goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design Expertise: Ability to build experiences that encourage positive player behavior, especially on features without comparables in the market&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quantitative Skills: Intermediate statistics; able to assess when and how to use data, translate product issues into analytics tasks, set hypotheses, interpret data optimally, and visualize it in Excel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Critical, Analytical, and Creative Thinking: Outcome-driven with a strong focus on execution and an ambitious mentality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ex

&lt;p&gt;Scopely is looking for a superstar &lt;strong&gt;Game Design Director&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Star Trek Fleet Command team in Ireland, Spain, or the UK on a remote basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play, every day – whether in our work environments alongside talented colleagues or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing, and innovating in the mobile games industry, connecting millions of players around the world daily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Star Trek Fleet Command&lt;/strong&gt; is a standout success in the gaming industry. Launched in 2018, our in-house developed 4X MMO has continually evolved, earning its place as one of the top-grossing games on the market. Our next chapter is bold: we’re evolving the traditional 4X experience in STFC — and we need a bold design leader to shape the content and loops our players engage with on a daily basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Game Design Director on STFC, you’ll own the standards, direction, and experiences that define how millions of players experience growth and mastery across our monthly content releases and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Become the design owner and leader behind our content pipeline, directing designers and live ops specialists in crafting compelling experiences for our players&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide teams through the creative process, ensuring they can hit the vision of the game and deliver upon player and product needs with accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and mentor designers in systems and economy design to elevate our standards and craft incredible experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fostering a high-performance culture within the department through leadership, people development, and team engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape the design process to ensure the standards of players are met and exceeded&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with design leaders to shape the future of the game economy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Experienced, driven and passionate Designers, Product Managers, Analysts, and Engineers to implement features which aim to advance the genre&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate performance using data, player feedback, and your own playtest experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design for scale: plan for long-term content extensibility and system health&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of game design leadership experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in F2P systems design and progression modelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience designing systems or economies for live, F2P games (preferably MMO, 4X, or strategy genres)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep experience and mastery of complex game economies in F2P&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent leadership and team management skills, with the ability to inspire and motivate a design team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of delivering clear, consistent creative direction and managerial feedback that elevates others&#39; work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with all aspects of game design discipline: concept, game progression, interface, monetization, and retention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to translate KPI targets and data into design direction for teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mastery of spreadsheets and confidence in balancing power curves, pacing, and resource flow&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working cross-functionally and navigating live production environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A positive, thoughtful, and collaborative approach to game development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep unders

&lt;p&gt;作为一名战斗策划，您将根据项目的目标与方向，参与定义游戏在战斗和沙盘两个核心方向的基础体验。您将以玩家为中心，推进战斗与沙盘系统的设计与平衡，保证玩法的策略深度和持久吸引力。您需要与项目组各部门高效协作，推动方案实现并持续优化内容品质。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;我们是谁&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;我们团队始终坚信以玩家体验为核心，这不仅是工作的基础，更是驱动我们不断创新的动力。如果你热衷于探索前沿设计，喜欢带来影响深远的玩法创新，欢迎加入我们，一起定义新世代社交策略体验！&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;您的影响&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;定义战斗与沙盘体验&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;以项目前景和目标为导向，参与战斗系统和沙盘玩法的整体框架设计，切实影响玩家的主要互动节奏、策略深度和沉浸反馈，助推产品体验达成行业领先。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;构建与平衡战斗与沙盘系统&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;拟定并完善战斗规则、单位/技能/地图机制等基础内容，协同数值策划推进平衡测试与落地，确保玩法公平有趣、策略丰富。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;推动创新与验证原型&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;积极提出前瞻性设计设想，将创意理念转化为可操作的原型，并参与多轮体验验证与调优，助力玩法体系不断自我突破。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;跨团队协作与高效实现&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;主动联合程序、美术、UI/UX等多职能团队，推进战斗与沙盘系统的高效协作开发与品质管控，确保方案与整体产品战略保持一致。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;关注玩家与市场动态&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;跟进主流竞品和行业趋势，结合实际数据与玩家反馈，持续优化设计内容，提升玩家体验与系统可玩性。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;岗位职责&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;深度参与从0到1的方案设计，清晰梳理系统结构和功能细节，保障玩法基础可靠可拓展。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;负责核心机制的文档输出与细化，协助数值团队定义关键参数与成长体系。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;主动关注和分析主流竞品的玩法思路，结合玩家偏好和市场趋势提出可落地的创新点，推动功能快速上线、反复迭代。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;与项目相关各部门密切沟通，确保设计方案能够以较高还原度和效率开发落地。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;敏锐洞察玩家需求，参与数据分析和用户调研，对系统功能体验持续进行优化、跟踪与调整。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;任职要求&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;本科及以上学历，2年以上战斗方向的游戏策划经验，有完整移动端项目从立项到上线的实践经历优先。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;拥有良好的逻辑思维、玩法建模及文档输出能力，能独立负责细化方案与推进开发协作。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;热衷游戏及玩法创新，对市场主流产品有深入体验及见解。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;积极主动，善于跨部门沟通，具备团队协作精神和推动复杂方案落地的执行力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;加分项&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;有头部产品核心策划经验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;深度体验游戏，对玩家需求和IP特色有独到理解。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;具备复杂系统数据与体验调优能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;熟悉A/B测试、用户数据分析方法，能基于结果提出有效优化建议。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;能阅读或撰写英文设计文档，有国际化手游项目经验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;用工性质：与专业人事服务公司FESCO Adecco签订劳动合同.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At Riot, engineers bring deep knowledge of specific technical areas but also value the opportunity to work in a variety of broader domains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Software Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; on the Unreal Ecosystem team, you will work with a passionate team of engineers in the support of plugins, tools and systems that empower all developers and collaborators to make the best game experiences for our players.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Unreal Ecosystem (UnEco) team collaborates with partners across Riot, all contributing to a stronger, more efficient Unreal development environment. You’ll navigate diverse technical challenges, ramping up quickly on new topics and solving complex problems in ways that empower both developers and, ultimately, our players.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role is open to remote candidates, with core hours aligned to Sydney time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the on-call rotation within core working hours; resolve game developer workflows &amp;amp; identify points of improvements from hands on support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain software systems with a focus on quality, reliability, and maintainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write clear documentation and communicate technical details across teams and disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Uphold a high standard of technical support excellence. Participate in code reviews, write unit/integration tests, and contribute to continuous improvement of team practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years experience in professional software development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of professional experience and proficiency with C++&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with game development teams or adjacent industries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Unreal engine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of software engineering fundamentals (data structures, algorithms, concurrency, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication within and across teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in English&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core working hours are anchored to Sydney Time: 9am-5pm AEST (Apr-Oct) / 10am-6pm AEDT (Oct-Apr)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Desired Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency or conversational ability in Mandarin (a plus for collaboration with APAC partners)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For this role, you&#39;ll find success through craft expertise, a collaborative spirit, and decision-making that prioritizes the delight of players. We will be looking at your past studies, experience, and your personal relationship with games. If you embody player empathy and care about players&#39; experiences, this could be your role!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 300;&quot;&gt;Riot Games fosters a player and workplace experience that values teamwork embodied by the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.leagueoflegends.com/en-us/event/league-of-legends-code-of-conduct/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summoner&#39;s Code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; and &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://playvalorant.com/en-us/news/announcements/valorant-community-code/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;. Our culture embraces differences as a strength, and our values are the guiding principles for how we approach work. We are committed to putting diversity and inclusion (D&amp;amp;I) at the center of everything we do, and promoting a fair and collaborative culture where Rioters treat one another with dignity and respect. We encourage you to read more about our value of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.rio

&lt;p&gt;Scopely is looking for a Software Engineer, Web/Full Stack to join our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Pokémon GO Engineering&lt;/strong&gt; team in Mexico City on a hybrid basis, working 3 days a week from the hub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Scopely, we care deeply about what we do and want to inspire play every day - whether in our work environments alongside our talented colleagues or through our deep connections with our communities of players. We are a global team of game lovers who are developing, publishing and innovating the mobile games industry, connecting millions of people around the world daily.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will be a key individual contributor focused on developing and scaling the critical web applications and player-facing features that support the global Pokémon GO community. You will build highly interactive, responsive web experiences while ensuring seamless data integration with our backend services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an adventurous, execution-focused Software Engineer, Web/Full Stack. We look for engineers with a strong technical background, great execution, and a self-starter mentality. The ideal candidate loves to jump into the unknown, clarify ambiguities, quickly learn from failures, and break down vague ideas into concrete tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an individual contributor on the web applications team, you will be responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Building well-designed, highly performant, and reusable web applications and UI components using &lt;strong&gt;React&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Next.js&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;TypeScript&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Crafting delightful, low-latency user interfaces that deliver a seamless experience across desktop and mobile browsers for millions of active players.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementing and maintaining backend services and APIs that reliably serve data to your web applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing and implementing efficient client-server contracts utilizing a modern suite of network protocols, including &lt;strong&gt;HTTP&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;GraphQL&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;gRPC&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating closely between engineering, design, and product teams to ensure the goals of the product are aligned with the delivered web features.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating in code reviews, writing comprehensive unit tests, and conducting troubleshooting to ensure uptime for live production systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional team members and stakeholders to cultivate strong working relationships, including regular and reliable attendance and participation in meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Required in-office 3 days per week, based in Mexico City, Mexico.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS, MS, or PhD in Computer Science, or a related technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of professional industry experience in full-stack web development within a technology or gaming company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong, production-proven experience building web applications with &lt;strong&gt;TypeScript&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;React&lt;/strong&gt;, and framework architectures like &lt;strong&gt;Next.js&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of client-server application domains, with practical experience querying data and managing network communication via &lt;strong&gt;HTTP&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;GraphQL&lt;/strong&gt;, and &lt;strong&gt;gRPC&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to integrate modern AI coding assistants into your daily workflow to streamline development, while ensuring all AI-generated contributions meet team standards for safety, architecture, and reliability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent probl

&lt;p&gt;作为一名资深文案策划，您将负责构建和丰富基于全新重社交手游的世界观与叙事体验。您将确保故事情节、角色塑造和包装不仅绝对契合原 IP 的宏大设定，更能完美融入游戏的核心玩法中，为游戏赋予深刻的沉浸感与持久的情感共鸣。您将跨职能协作，确保叙事内容能够高质量、生动地呈现在玩家面前。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 data-section-id=&quot;utd37w&quot; data-start=&quot;806&quot; data-end=&quot;824&quot;&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;8oibwx&quot; data-start=&quot;826&quot; data-end=&quot;840&quot;&gt;核心叙事框架与内容设计&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;841&quot; data-end=&quot;934&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1mmicf2&quot; data-start=&quot;841&quot; data-end=&quot;894&quot;&gt;深度参与产品叙事框架、内容结构及核心角色表达的规划与设计，推动叙事 DEMO 方案高效实现与快速落地。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;vtjg3v&quot; data-start=&quot;895&quot; data-end=&quot;934&quot;&gt;负责长期内容体验的叙事包装与表达设计，确保内容风格统一且具备持续演进能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;z2q8ye&quot; data-start=&quot;936&quot; data-end=&quot;951&quot;&gt;高品质文案撰写与内容表达&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;952&quot; data-end=&quot;1033&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1aipl1g&quot; data-start=&quot;952&quot; data-end=&quot;1001&quot;&gt;负责产品内核心文案的撰写与包装，包括系统文本、角色语音文本（VO）、交互事件及长期运营内容等。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1uj4pvn&quot; data-start=&quot;1002&quot; data-end=&quot;1033&quot;&gt;确保整体内容表达在语气、结构与沉浸感层面保持高质量一致性。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;1njhp1a&quot; data-start=&quot;1035&quot; data-end=&quot;1047&quot;&gt;内容研究与创新探索&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1048&quot; data-end=&quot;1124&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;cdpggt&quot; data-start=&quot;1048&quot; data-end=&quot;1087&quot;&gt;深度研究行业内主流产品的叙事表达方式与内容趋势，探索创新性的互动内容体验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1v3prx2&quot; data-start=&quot;1088&quot; data-end=&quot;1124&quot;&gt;结合用户反馈与市场变化，为长期内容迭代提供高质量创意方向与表达方案。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;2vvy1f&quot; data-start=&quot;1126&quot; data-end=&quot;1139&quot;&gt;跨团队协作与落地推进&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1140&quot; data-end=&quot;1214&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;ecdms7&quot; data-start=&quot;1140&quot; data-end=&quot;1177&quot;&gt;编写高标准叙事文档与内容需求文档，清晰定义视听表达需求与内容实现标准。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1mjckvh&quot; data-start=&quot;1178&quot; data-end=&quot;1214&quot;&gt;主动协调美术、音频、设计、工程与制作团队，高效推进关键内容方案落地。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;a0vzwk&quot; data-start=&quot;1216&quot; data-end=&quot;1225&quot;&gt;用户体验洞察&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1226&quot; data-end=&quot;1289&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;fy4asa&quot; data-start=&quot;1226&quot; data-end=&quot;1261&quot;&gt;深入理解目标用户体验需求，通过内容表达增强产品沉浸感与长期参与感。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1fkvn28&quot; data-start=&quot;1262&quot; data-end=&quot;1289&quot;&gt;系统性评估内容方案的创新性、可行性与整体体验价值。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1 data-section-id=&quot;6uehu5&quot; data-start=&quot;1296&quot; data-end=&quot;1321&quot;&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul data-start=&quot;1323&quot; data-end=&quot;1590&quot;&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;ushozx&quot; data-start=&quot;1323&quot; data-end=&quot;1356&quot;&gt;本科及以上学历，6年以上互动娱乐或游戏内容设计/文案策划经验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;1w6u629&quot; data-start=&quot;1357&quot; data-end=&quot;1402&quot;&gt;具备大型在线产品或长线运营内容项目经验，曾参与新项目从研发到上线或核心开发阶段者优先。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;18a03r8&quot; data-start=&quot;1403&quot; data-end=&quot;1442&quot;&gt;拥有扎实的文学功底与叙事设计能力，能够独立完成长线内容规划与角色表达设计。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;2dmlzk&quot; data-start=&quot;1443&quot; data-end=&quot;1480&quot;&gt;具备优秀的跨团队沟通与协作能力，能够将抽象概念转化为可执行的内容需求。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;2phrxv&quot; data-start=&quot;1481&quot; data-end=&quot;1518&quot;&gt;具备优秀的文字审美与内容把控能力，能够在复杂项目环境下保持高质量输出。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;5fd4lp&quot; data-start=&quot;1519&quot; data-end=&quot;1541&quot;&gt;对互动体验与沉浸式内容表达具备深入理解。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;x26ord&quot; data-start=&quot;1542&quot; data-end=&quot;1570&quot;&gt;具备良好的逻辑分析能力、信息整合能力与文档表达能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-section-id=&quot;cxgwgw&quot; data-start=&q

&lt;p&gt;作为一名系统策划，您将肩负项目城池发展和核心系统玩法的设计工作，围绕成长、建造、资源流、功能解锁等内容，为游戏世界注入持久成长驱动力。您需要以玩家为中心，完善系统框架，设计富有策略深度的城市发展玩法，持续优化成长体验与动力体系，为产品生命周期注入源源不绝的新鲜感。您将与团队高效协作，推动高质量交付并持续提升团队创新能力。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;我们是谁&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;我们以玩家体验为根本，不断追求设计创新。这里是你释放创新想法、赋能核心系统、改变传统玩法生态的大舞台。如果你渴望挑战、热爱运营和创新，期待你加入我们并共创未来！&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;您的影响&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;定义城池发展体验&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;以项目目标为指引，主导城市成长、建筑升级、功能体系等玩法核心模块设计，营造激励成长与多元选择并存的体验节奏。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;构建系统与成长闭环&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;搭建资源生产、消耗、成长及动力体系，让玩家在可感知的反馈循环中体验长期目标与阶段感成就。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;推动系统创新与落地&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;将创意转化为高落地性的系统方案，主导原型验证与功能优化，不断提升成长体系与城池玩法的策略深度。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;跨团队协作推动优质交付&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;联合美术、程序、数值、UI等多团队，保障系统设计与开发同步迭代、品质稳定，并持续聚焦用户体验提升。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;数据驱动与行业洞察&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;关注市场标杆产品及行业趋势，结合数据分析和玩家反馈持续优化系统内容与成长曲线，提升竞争力与可玩性。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;岗位职责&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;参与城池、建筑、资源及系统功能的0到1设计，实现成长、建造、运营等核心模块的系统化梳理与体验优化。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;负责制定成长体系、资源产消与动力闭环相关文档与设计原型，把控系统机制的全周期推演和调优。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;联合数值策划完成系统数值结构、资源分配及发展节奏的详细设定，实现公平性与可玩性平衡。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;跟踪竞品并提炼差异化优势，提出城建及玩法创新点，高效转换为可执行的功能方案，推动快速迭代与落地。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;配合研发、美术等协作团队，确保方案落地还原度和功能流畅，持续推动体验打磨和流程优化。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;收集数据、分析玩家反馈，系统性评估和优化设计内容，推动城池发展和核心系统可持续进化。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;任职要求&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;本科及以上学历，2年以上系统策划或城市成长相关经验，参与过上线产品的核心系统设计与迭代优先。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;熟悉城池建设、养成、系统成长等相关机制，对经济系统、成长体系有系统认知与实操经验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;拥有扎实的玩法设计、系统梳理、文档输出与流程拆解能力，能独立承担重点模块并协作推进复盘。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;关心用户长期体验，对成长驱动力和多元可玩性有深入洞察，善于结合数据分析优化系统内容。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;具备出色的沟通与团队协作能力，积极推动方案高效落地。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;加分项&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;有城市建设、成长模拟、策略或重社交手游的玩法及系统策划经验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;具备大型成长/经济系统模型搭建、数据调优或A/B测试实际经验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;有国际化项目、海外用户洞察或多文化团队协作能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;能撰写或阅读英文系统策划文档。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;我们的福利&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;我们倡导健康平衡的工作与生活，提供有竞争力的带薪休假、灵活办公方式及多元保险福利。团队关注多元与包容性氛围，鼓励创新协作，让每一位成员都能获得成长和成就。与我们一起，见证并驱动一款创新大作的诞生吧！&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;用工性质：与专业人事服务公司FESCO Adecco签订劳动合同&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Riot Games was established in 2006 by entrepreneurial gamers who believe that player-focused game development can result in great games. In 2009, Riot released its debut title&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;League of Legends&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;to critical and player acclaim. As the most played video game in the world, over 100 million play every month. Players form the foundation of our community and it’s for them that we continue to evolve and improve the&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;League of Legends&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for humble but ambitious, razor-sharp professionals who can teach us a thing or two. We promise to return the favor. Like us, you take play seriously; you’re passionate about games. We embrace those who see things differently, aren’t afraid to experiment, and who have a healthy disregard for constraints.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&#39;s where you come in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Principal Game Designer&lt;/strong&gt; at Riot, you will shape, refine, and elevate player experiences through clear design vision, expert craft judgment, and deep player empathy. Your leadership, strategic thinking, and ability to work across disciplines will help teams create experiences that feel cohesive, distinctive, and worthy of players’ time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Principal Game Designer at Riot China Studio, you will define and guide the game’s overall design vision for a fast-paced new title. You will work closely with a lean internal team and external development partners to ensure gameplay, feature direction, and product execution align with Riot’s quality bar and player expectations. You will make high-conviction decisions about core game design, audience needs, and IP authenticity while helping the team move with speed in an ambiguous development environment. You will report to the Head of China Studio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve the game’s holistic design vision, core gameplay direction, and player experience goals from concept through development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish clear design principles, frameworks, and quality bars that guide feature development, player experience decisions, and long-term product direction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and guide major design decisions, ensuring systems and features align with player needs, product goals, and Riot’s quality expectations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate player insight, product context, market understanding, and development realities into clear design direction and strategic priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with internal developers and external co-development teams to align on design intent, execution quality, and iteration plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate trade-offs, identify risks early, and make agile decisions that help the team respond to feedback, data, and changing development needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solve ambiguous, high-impact design problems and create clarity for cross-functional partners across design, production, art, and leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Raise the craft bar by mentoring other designers, giving high-quality feedback, and influencing how the team approaches game design without relying on formal people management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of professional experience in game design, product leadership, or related game development roles, including significant responsibility on shipped titles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience defining gameplay vision, feature direction, or holistic player experience for a live, in-development, or shipped game&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience working closely with external development partners, co-development teams, or publishers to deliver high-quality game experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ability to operate in ambiguous environments and drive alignment across design, production, and cross-function

&lt;p&gt;As a Technical Artist for Tools/Pipeline, you&#39;ll employ your expert-level knowledge of 3D tools to build tools, maintain pipelines, and provide technical support for artists on their most critical missions. You will establish and improve the systems, tools, rigs, assets, and workflows that unleash the creativity of our artists and allow the production of the best possible art content for our players. And you will critique work, mentor fellow Rioters, and foster the long-term growth of a group of artists.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Principal Tools &amp;amp; Pipeline Technical Artist&lt;/strong&gt; on an unpublished R&amp;amp;D product, you&#39;ll focus on building the tools and tech used for content development on an upcoming game project. This will involve building pipelines and workflows for DCC (Digital Content Creation) software, and consulting with art to discover the best possible solutions to the challenges the project team faces. You report directly to the Technical Art Director of the project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate a cohesive vision and standard for art vision, artistic workflows, and pipelines based on the Art Director and Creative Director’s visions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in evaluating new systems and technology that support the artistic, product, and gameplay goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help to identify new opportunities to incorporate technology to increase art workflow efficiency and unlock new creative opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Amplify artistic capabilities while maintaining efficient and sustainable memory and performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the team in identifying new opportunities to incorporate technology to increase art workflow efficiency and unlock new creative opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with other Technical Art leaders at the studio to develop a cohesive vision and shared standards across the Technical Art discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Required Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of professional experience as a technical artist in games or related industries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional experience working within the games industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in industry-standard content creation tools, such as Maya, and commercial game engines (i.e. Unreal, Unity, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in modern scripting languages and related UI frameworks, such as Python and PyQt/PySide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience problem-solving and communicating with multiple art disciplines and acting as an ambassador between art and engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Desired Qualifications:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in game development using Unreal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing shaders and working in HLSL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of 3D modeling, efficient UV layouts, and materials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of current console art pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When submitting your application, please provide a portfolio of your high-quality tech art - including stylized artwork. And as a part of the application process, you may also be asked to complete an art test.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For this role, you&#39;ll find success through craft expertise, a collaborative spirit, and decision-making that prioritizes the delight of players. We will be looking at your past studies, experience, and your personal relationship with games. If you embody player empathy and care about players&#39; experiences, this could be your role!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Perks:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Riot focuses on work/life balance, shown by our open paid time off policy and other perks such as flexible work schedules. We offer medical, dental, and life insurance, parental leave for you, your spouse/domestic partner, and chi

&lt;p&gt;All Game Designers at Riot have a base set of skills: you design, tweak, and optimize the player experience. Your analytical skills, player insight, and creativity aid in crafting in- and out-of-game experiences that engage and surprise players.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Technical Game Designer&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;on an unpublished R&amp;amp;D product, you excel in designing exceptional experiences with high novelty and filled with unique challenges to overcome. You partner with other designers, artists, and engineers to create and iterate on a variety of memorable content types for players. You will also help designers and engineers build and expand our engine capabilities creating powerful tools that can empower other designers to create their own unique experiences.&amp;nbsp;You will partner closely with designers and engineers to translate ambitious creative visions into actionable, scalable technical designs. Through a mix of mentorship and content reviews, you also ensure that local designers are building the game with strong technical rigor. Reporting directly to the Lead Technical Designer, your contributions will elevate the capabilities of the entire team on this ambitious project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively to design, prototype and deliver compelling player experiences from the beginning to the end of an activity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a hands-on owner for a portion of systems and other content that pushes for novel, unique, and challenging player experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with engineering to define the technical strategy and execution of content systems and reusable content tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build out solutions to design problems that require a deep level of technical expertise and leaving those problems with the ability to teach others how to work in those spaces in the future.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, advocate, and enforce a system of organizational excellence in content creation that allows for the long-term sustainability of software without being cumbersome to rapid prototyping culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement gameplay workflows and tools within Unreal Engine to enable designers and artists to rapidly prototype and iterate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify technical risks, develop mitigation strategies, and communicate clearly with team leadership and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure high-quality implementation of complex gameplay systems, promoting performance, scalability, and maintainability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in professional Technical Game Design or related Tech Design or Engineering roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in content design in real-time games&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience shipping high-quality titles using Unreal Engine, demonstrating expertise in Blueprints, scripting, and technical workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with C++ and C#&lt;/li&gt;
